==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weregild
<hw>Were"gild`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>wergild</ets>; <ets>wer</ets> a man, value set on a man's life +
<ets>gild</ets> payment of money; akin to G. <ets>wehrgeld</ets>.
⟦root⟧285. See <er>Were</er> a man, and <er>Geld</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>The price of a man's
head; a compensation paid of a man killed, partly to the king for the
loss of a subject, partly to the lord of a vassal, and partly to the
next of kin. It was paid by the murderer.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>weregeld</asp>, <asp>weregelt</asp>, etc.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

